There's importance
       to speaking the truth.

986
00:44:38.676 --> 00:44:41.136
And some people are not
          gonna like that.

987
00:44:41.136 --> 00:44:44.556
And that's something
   you just have to get used to.

988
00:44:46.225 --> 00:44:47.976
-At any chance that we feel

989
00:44:47.976 --> 00:44:51.146
we can use our music
            to give back.

990
00:44:51.146 --> 00:44:53.232
we are not only
           happy to do it.

991
00:44:53.232 --> 00:44:55.734
we actually almost hunger
              to do it

992
00:44:55.734 --> 00:44:58.153
so that you can feel
           that your music

993
00:44:58.153 --> 00:45:00.906
is not just
        for your own pleasure

994
00:45:00.906 --> 00:45:04.868
and hopefully that your words.
             your songs.

995
00:45:04.868 --> 00:45:07.204
will also touch a chord
             into people

996
00:45:07.204 --> 00:45:11.041
to increase their empathy
         and their humanity.

997
00:45:11.041 --> 00:45:13.293
The Lilith Fair tour
       was really eye-opening

998
00:45:13.293 --> 00:45:16.171
for so many of us women
       out there making music

999
00:45:16.171 --> 00:45:19.133
'cause I think we'd been
    out there in our tour busses

1000
00:45:19.133 --> 00:45:21.719
with our bands traveling
          around. you know.

1001
00:45:21.719 --> 00:45:23.929
like. in space.
           in outer space.

1002
00:45:23.929 --> 00:45:25.472
in our own
        little rocket ships.

1003
00:45:25.472 --> 00:45:28.058
And all of a sudden we all
      landed in this one place

1004
00:45:28.058 --> 00:45:29.309
and we came off our busses

1005
00:45:29.309 --> 00:45:32.146
and we were actually
        finally able to meet.

1006
00:45:32.146 --> 00:45:37.151
and you realized that there
     was a sisterhood out there.

1007
00:45:39.153 --> 00:45:42.156
-By 1996. there were quite
         a few more females

1008
00:45:42.156 --> 00:45:43.741
that were getting
          played at radio.

1009
00:45:43.741 --> 00:45:45.909
One of them was
         Alanis Morissette.

1010
00:45:45.909 --> 00:45:48.454
Aimee Mann. and another was
          Sarah McLachlan.

1011
00:45:48.454 --> 00:45:54.877
- I'd no longer be
           in your mind

1012
00:45:54.877 --> 00:45:59.798
The difficult kind
         but you won't see

1013
00:45:59.798 --> 00:46:02.176
-I remember vividly
           Sarah McLachlan

1014
00:46:02.176 --> 00:46:03.469
calling me and saying.

1015
00:46:03.469 --> 00:46:06.054
"Have you ever tried to have
       someone open up for you

1016
00:46:06.054 --> 00:46:07.431
that's a woman?
      The promoters are saying

1017
00:46:07.431 --> 00:46:09.391
you can't have more
      than one woman on a bill.

1018
00:46:09.391 --> 00:46:12.269
and I'm going
         to disprove them."

1019
00:46:12.269 --> 00:46:14.938
-Now. some business types
 said. "Oh. that'll never work.

1020
00:46:14.938 --> 00:46:18.192
Nobody will buy tickets
 to all women all summer long."

1021
00:46:18.192 --> 00:46:20.277
Well. 20.000 people
          showed up today.

1022
00:46:20.277 --> 00:46:24.490
and the Lilith Fair
        will visit 35 cities.

1023
00:46:25.532 --> 00:46:28.452
-It was just women
      who commercially do well.

1024
00:46:28.452 --> 00:46:31.455
We run our businesses.
           We make money.

1025
00:46:31.455 --> 00:46:34.958
So why are you men deciding
       what can and can't be?

1026
00:46:34.958 --> 00:46:39.046
But what you don't think about
     is the kid that's out there

1027
00:46:39.046 --> 00:46:42.549
in the audience
     looking at that and going.

1028
00:46:42.549 --> 00:46:43.675
"I can do that.

1029
00:46:43.675 --> 00:46:45.511
I can get up and play guitar

1030
00:46:45.511 --> 00:46:49.348
and have a band behind me
          and be the boss."

1031
00:46:50.140 --> 00:46:51.975
-Tell you what.

1032
00:46:51.975 --> 00:46:55.229
I was out there all the way
        up there on that hill

1033
00:46:55.229 --> 00:46:57.898
in Lilith Fair when I saw
        Sheryl Crow play here

1034
00:46:57.898 --> 00:47:00.025
two nights in a row.

1035
00:47:00.025 --> 00:47:01.527
It honestly changed my life.

1036
00:47:01.527 --> 00:47:05.364
and I would not be the artist
   that I am without Sheryl Crow

1037
00:47:05.364 --> 00:47:07.324
and the influence
        that she's had on me.

1038
00:47:07.324 --> 00:47:09.159
And then to get to a place
       where she's kind enough

1039
00:47:09.159 --> 00:47:10.911
to be my friend
         and give me advice

1040
00:47:10.911 --> 00:47:12.913
and teach me things
         and sing with me --

1041
00:47:12.913 --> 00:47:14.915
I can't even get
         my head around it.

1042
00:47:16.166 --> 00:47:20.879
-I just was astounded
 that she was so rock and roll.

1043
00:47:20.879 --> 00:47:22.130
And you never questioned

1044
00:47:22.130 --> 00:47:24.216
whether or not
        Sheryl was the boss.

1045
00:47:24.216 --> 00:47:26.176
and I was so drawn to that --

1046
00:47:26.176 --> 00:47:30.138
you know. as a young woman.
        so influenced by it.

1047
00:47:30.138 --> 00:47:32.599
Seeing her play the bass.
    you know. I'll never forget.

1048
00:47:32.599 --> 00:47:34.393
like. picking up
     that bass guitar and. like.

1049
00:47:34.393 --> 00:47:36.061
telling the guy
        I was in a band with.

1050
00:47:36.061 --> 00:47:40.899
"Yeah. I played bass" --

1051
00:47:41.984 --> 00:47:43.819
Because I had to learn
       the "Leaving Las Vegas"

1052
00:47:43.819 --> 00:47:45.112
bass line.

1053
00:47:45.112 --> 00:47:46.446
and just thinking. like.

1054
00:47:46.446 --> 00:47:48.323
"Yeah. this is it.
     this is what I want to do.

1055
00:47:48.323 --> 00:47:49.533
I want to front a band
              like this

1056
00:47:49.533 --> 00:47:51.368
and I want to have
         an electric guitar

1057
00:47:51.368 --> 00:47:53.912
and I want to play bass
    and I want to be a rock star

1058
00:47:53.912 --> 00:47:56.415
like Sheryl Crow."

1059
00:47:56.415 --> 00:47:58.208
-I think we should
         give it up to Sarah

1060
00:47:58.208 --> 00:48:00.544
for putting this
        whole thing together.

1061
00:48:00.544 --> 00:48:04.423
Anywhere where people are
 comfortable with who they are.

1062
00:48:04.423 --> 00:48:06.842
even on the Lilith Fair.
         you could look out

1063
00:48:06.842 --> 00:48:08.468
and you would see
         families out there.

1064
00:48:08.468 --> 00:48:11.513
and you would see girls
           and their moms.

1065
00:48:11.513 --> 00:48:14.892
and you would see
         a lot of lesbians.

1066
00:48:17.477 --> 00:48:20.772
-I like that about Sheryl
              so much.

1067
00:48:20.772 --> 00:48:22.524
that she holds her space.

1068
00:48:22.524 --> 00:48:24.651
She's straight as an arrow.
              but God.

1069
00:48:24.651 --> 00:48:25.527
the lesbians love Sheryl.

1070
00:48:25.527 --> 00:48:27.154
She's important
          to queer people.

1071
00:48:27.154 --> 00:48:28.572
and when you're important
          to queer people.

1072
00:48:28.572 --> 00:48:32.075
it means you're on the cutting
        edge of the real shit

1073
00:48:32.075 --> 00:48:35.370
of what's really going on.

1074
00:48:35.370 --> 00:48:38.206
-After that tour. which had
       been really successful

1075
00:48:38.206 --> 00:48:40.167
and really fun.
         I came home to L.A.

1076
00:48:40.167 --> 00:48:42.586
and I was engaged
      with a casting director.

1077
00:48:42.586 --> 00:48:47.090
somebody I met on
 the "Leaving Las Vegas" video.

1078
00:48:47.090 --> 00:48:50.385
-This is the young man
     that Sheryl was engaged to.

1079
00:48:50.385 --> 00:48:52.346
-That was back in. uh...

1080
00:48:52.346 --> 00:48:53.972
-That was in 1995.

1081
00:48:55.265 --> 00:48:58.185
Can you maybe turn that off?

1082
00:48:58.185 --> 00:49:00.270
-I was just starting
             my career.

1083
00:49:00.270 --> 00:49:01.563
and it was starting
            to take off.

1084
00:49:01.563 --> 00:49:05.400
and it's really difficult
      for someone to sort of be

1085
00:49:05.400 --> 00:49:09.321
swept up in that and still
      keep their sense of self.

1086
00:49:09.321 --> 00:49:11.323
We were just better
        as friends; in fact.

1087
00:49:11.323 --> 00:49:13.700
by the time we got engaged.
       I feel like we probably

1088
00:49:13.700 --> 00:49:15.035
were pulling apart.

1089
00:49:15.035 --> 00:49:16.662
I'd been gone for so long.

1090
00:49:16.662 --> 00:49:19.456
I did have a couple of songs
     on the "Sheryl Crow" record

1091
00:49:19.456 --> 00:49:22.292
that were inspired
         by our relationship

1092
00:49:22.292 --> 00:49:23.794
becoming more platonic.

1093
00:49:23.794 --> 00:49:28.840
I woke this morning.
         now I understand

1094
00:49:28.840 --> 00:49:34.638
What it means to give
     your life to just one man

1095
00:49:34.638 --> 00:49:39.559
Afraid of feeling nothing.
      no bees or butterflies

1096
00:49:39.559 --> 00:49:45.482
My head is full of questions
 and my house is full of lies

1097
00:49:45.482 --> 00:49:51.989
And this is home

1098
00:49:51.989 --> 00:49:56.702
Home

1099
00:49:56.702 --> 00:49:59.496
This is home

1100
00:49:59.496 --> 00:50:02.916
I think part of my pull
           is always that

1101
00:50:02.916 --> 00:50:04.668
I really like the...
              the hang.

1102
00:50:04.668 --> 00:50:07.129
I like the camaraderie
           with the guys.

1103
00:50:07.129 --> 00:50:08.255
and part of me is like.

1104
00:50:08.255 --> 00:50:10.132
I don't want
        to miss out on that.

1105
00:50:10.132 --> 00:50:12.259
So I decided I would just...

1106
00:50:12.259 --> 00:50:15.387
pick up and move to New York
       and change my scenery.

1107
00:50:15.387 --> 00:50:19.224
And you can probably
         see a pattern here.

1108
00:50:33.780 --> 00:50:38.952
Somebody said
        you gotta get away

1109
00:50:42.622 --> 00:50:47.169
Don't wanna
        go back home again

1110
00:50:48.545 --> 00:50:50.714
I set up a studio
    in the Meatpacking District.

1111
00:50:50.714 --> 00:50:54.593
I mean. it was just
   a very colorful neighborhood.

1112
00:50:54.593 --> 00:50:57.345
-It was warehouses
            and butchers

1113
00:50:57.345 --> 00:50:59.264
and carcasses hanging.

1114
00:50:59.264 --> 00:51:01.391
You could smell the blood
           on the streets.

1115
00:51:01.391 --> 00:51:04.227
-Jeff and I started
         working with Trina

1116
00:51:04.227 --> 00:51:05.479
in a studio that we set up

1117
00:51:05.479 --> 00:51:08.273
in this building
          called The Globe.

1118
00:51:08.273 --> 00:51:10.400
-She had bought
         all this equipment.

1119
00:51:10.400 --> 00:51:12.569
It hadn't seasoned
         into the room yet.

1120
00:51:12.569 --> 00:51:15.280
It takes a little while
     for gear to get comfortable

1121
00:51:15.280 --> 00:51:16.698
and bugs to get worked out.

1122
00:51:16.698 --> 00:51:20.702
yet we were going forward
     and cutting a record there.

1123
00:51:33.340 --> 00:51:36.551
Antigone laid across
             the road

1124
00:51:36.551 --> 00:51:39.387
-Now the celebrity
            is locked in.

1125
00:51:39.387 --> 00:51:41.807
I mean. the celebrity machine.
        not the human being.

1126
00:51:41.807 --> 00:51:44.684
so now she's really
           got to deliver.

1127
00:51:44.684 --> 00:51:52.567
It's laughter that comes up
        when I cry for you

1128
00:51:52.567 --> 00:52:00.408
And this heart may love
      again before it learns

1129
00:52:00.408 --> 00:52:03.120
"Globe Sessions."
         of all the records.

1130
00:52:03.120 --> 00:52:04.579
was the most kind of pure.

1131
00:52:04.579 --> 00:52:06.873
I don't want to say. like.
            barfing out.

1132
00:52:06.873 --> 00:52:10.001
but I mean. everything was
      so close to the surface.

1133
00:52:10.001 --> 00:52:11.628
so immediate.

1134
00:52:11.628 --> 00:52:15.465
I've gotten used to
          crash and burn

1135
00:52:18.677 --> 00:52:25.142
Yes. I've gotten used to
        the crash and burn

1136
00:52:25.142 --> 00:52:26.643
A lot of that came out.

1137
00:52:26.643 --> 00:52:28.145
particularly
         in "Difficult Kind"

1138
00:52:28.145 --> 00:52:29.563
and definitely in
         "Crash and Burn" --

1139
00:52:29.563 --> 00:52:31.356
I mean. both of those songs.
          which I feel like

1140
00:52:31.356 --> 00:52:32.691
are kind of sister songs.

1141
00:52:32.691 --> 00:52:35.152
talk about somebody
         who's not that easy

1142
00:52:35.152 --> 00:52:36.528
to have a relationship with.

1143
00:52:36.528 --> 00:52:40.657
who is highly sensitive
        and highly emotional

1144
00:52:40.657 --> 00:52:42.534
and super tough and strong;

1145
00:52:42.534 --> 00:52:44.828
and the other aspect
        of being with someone

1146
00:52:44.828 --> 00:52:50.792
who has the job that I have is
 I'm just not around very much.

1147
00:52:53.712 --> 00:52:58.216
-There is a price to be paid
    for being gone all the time.

1148
00:52:58.216 --> 00:53:00.510
Obviously. I felt like
           it was worth it

1149
00:53:00.510 --> 00:53:03.513
because I'm still out here.
           but. you know.

1150
00:53:03.513 --> 00:53:05.974
it is difficult
       to stay away from home

1151
00:53:05.974 --> 00:53:07.350
so many times and so long.

1152
00:53:07.350 --> 00:53:09.186
-All I can say is I'm single

1153
00:53:09.186 --> 00:53:11.271
and I've been single
            a long time.

1154
00:53:11.271 --> 00:53:14.608
and that has got to be.
              you know.

1155
00:53:14.608 --> 00:53:17.777
the tour bus --
 my relationship with the road.

1156
00:53:17.777 --> 00:53:19.237
you know.
       it -- it is difficult.

1157
00:53:19.237 --> 00:53:20.739
it's a lot to ask for.

1158
00:53:20.739 --> 00:53:25.327
you know. to ask somebody
       to stay home and wait.

1159
00:53:25.327 --> 00:53:26.870
-We were both at this.

1160
00:53:26.870 --> 00:53:29.581
like. massive transition
            in our lives.

1161
00:53:29.581 --> 00:53:30.916
figuring out who we were.

1162
00:53:30.916 --> 00:53:33.543
what we wanted in life.
         and Sheryl's like.

1163
00:53:33.543 --> 00:53:35.837
"Oh. well.
      you should just move in!"

1164
00:53:35.837 --> 00:53:38.381
Like. "Why -- why are
     we spending so little time

1165
00:53:38.381 --> 00:53:42.010
together by going to dinner
        four nights a week?"

1166
00:53:42.010 --> 00:53:45.347
So I lived with Sheryl.

1167
00:53:45.347 --> 00:53:46.806
She might be the friend

1168
00:53:46.806 --> 00:53:51.269
that I've spent the most time
         watching her work.

1169
00:53:51.269 --> 00:53:53.271
We went on the ride together.

1170
00:53:53.271 --> 00:53:56.233
- Ooh

1171
00:53:56.233 --> 00:53:57.901
-And the best rock album is...

1172
00:53:57.901 --> 00:54:01.238
"The Globe Sessions."
            Sheryl Crow.

1173
00:54:01.238 --> 00:54:03.990
- Ooh

1174
00:54:06.576 --> 00:54:10.413
Ooh

1175
00:54:10.413 --> 00:54:14.751
Did you know when you go
      it's the perfect ending

